%% Batch Gateway - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4-ea.2/batch-gateway.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant API as API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP TLS (optional)
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proc as Batch Processor<br/>9090/TCP
    participant IGW as Inference Gateway<br/>(llm-d/GAIE)

    Note over Client,IGW: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission

    Client->>API: POST /v1/files (multipart)<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)<br/>Header: X-MaaS-User
    API->>S3: Upload JSONL file<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>API: File stored (file_id)
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {file_id}

    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches<br/>{input_file_id, endpoint, model}
    API->>Redis: Store batch metadata<br/>6379/TCP, Password auth
    API->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue<br/>6379/TCP, Password auth
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {batch_id, status: validating}

    Note over Client,IGW: Flow 2: Batch Job Processing

    Proc->>Redis: Poll priority queue (BRPOP)<br/>6379/TCP, Password auth
    Redis-->>Proc: Job dequeued
    Proc->>Redis: Get batch metadata<br/>6379/TCP, Password auth
    Redis-->>Proc: Batch details
    Proc->>S3: Download input JSONL<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    S3-->>Proc: Input file contents

    loop For each request in JSONL (Worker Pool)
        Proc->>IGW: POST inference request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, TLS 1.2+ / mTLS<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
        IGW-->>Proc: Inference response
        Proc->>Redis: Update progress status<br/>6379/TCP
    end

    Proc->>S3: Upload output JSONL<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Proc->>Redis: Update batch: completed<br/>6379/TCP, Password auth

    Note over Client,IGW: Flow 3: Batch Cancellation

    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>TLS 1.2+ (optional)
    API->>Redis: Remove from priority queue<br/>6379/TCP
    API->>Redis: Publish cancel event<br/>6379/TCP (event channel)
    API->>Redis: Update status: cancelling<br/>6379/TCP
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {status: cancelling}
